<StartAction>[The Dwarven worker looks up at you in irritation.]</Start> Whaddya' want? Can't ye see that I'm a bit busy here, cleaning up all this filth?!
<StartAction>[The Dwarf grunts at you, and returns to his work.]</Start>

Seems we had ourselves a rather nasty flood, that's what happened, ye blockheaded fool! My crew has been down here for three weeks now, tryin' to make sure the whole Market District isn't covered in this filth!

Not unless ye want to grab a hammer, and get down to yer waist in this mess! <StartAction>[The Dwarf looks at you disparagingly.]</Start> By the looks of ye, I don't think that's gonna happen... Now get out of here!
Aye, and it's a rougher one when a fool like yerself starts yappin' in my ear! Now get out of here, and let me get back to my work!

I done told ye all I know, <lad/lass>... Check out the northern part of the sewer. That's where I saw that Elven fellow last week, and might be what ye're lookin' for... Past that, don't think there's much I can do to help ye...
<StartAction>[The Dwarf looks at you suspiciously.]</Start> Now why would I know of such a thing, eh? Think just 'cause I work in the sewers, I'm a filthy murderer too?
Don't ye even start talkin' like that, <lad/lass>! Egbar the Dwarf don't take nicely to fools like ye making threats! But... but maybe I can help ye, if we can work out some sort of arrangement...

<StartAction>[The Dwarf narrows his eyes at you and grunts.]</Start> Now, I wouldn't be knowing about such things as murder, but I do know I saw an Elven fellow poking his head around here about a week ago...
He seemed a bit suspicious to me, but I don't make it my affair to go prying in others' business, so I let it be...
<StartAction>[The Dwarf grunts at you as a farewell, and returns to clearing out the flooded sewer.]</Start>
Well now, that depends... My memory's not what it used to be, but gold has a way of revitalizing it from time to time...
<StartAction>[Success]</Start> <StartAction>[The Dwarf gulps loudly, and cowers away from you.]</Start> Alright, alright! I'll tell ye what I know!
I saw an Elven fellow scurrying about in the northern part of the sewer last week, carrying some sort of heavy sack... Seemed mighty suspicious to me...

<StartAction>[Success] [The Dwarf beams at you and holds out a grimy hand to accept his payment.]</Start> I saw that Elven man roaming around the northern part of the sewers... and it looked to me like he was carrying some sort of heavy sack...
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> I'm afraid ye'll have to do better than that, <lad/lass>...

<StartAction>[Success] [The Dwarf beams at you and holds out a grimy hand to accept his payment.]</Start> I saw that Elven man roaming around the northern part of the sewers... and it looked to me like he was carrying some sort of heavy sack...

<StartAction>[Success] [The Dwarf beams at you and holds out a grimy hand to accept his payment.]</Start> I saw that Elven man roaming around the northern part of the sewers... and it looked to me like he was carrying some sort of heavy sack...
Might be what ye're lookin' for, <lad/lass>... I suggest ye give it a good search, and see what ye can find...
Now, I got to get back to me work, so why don't ye go about yer business?
<StartAction>[The Dwarf looks at you with glazed eyes.]</Start> Yeah, I think I might be able to help ye...

Sorry to have bothered you. I'll be on my way.
What happened down here?
I think I'll be on my way...
Anything I can do to help?
Sounds like a rough job...
I'm trying to find a body...
You're right... I'm sorry if I have offended you.
Why? What are you hiding, Dwarf?
No, no, no... You're not a suspect.
Interesting... I'll keep that in mind.
<StartAction>[Walk away.]</Start>
<StartAction>[Charisma]</Start> Did you happen to see where he went?
Thanks for nothing...
<StartAction>[Intimidate]</Start> How about I wring your filthy little neck!
<StartAction>[Persuade]</Start> Would 10 gold pieces refersh your memory?
<StartAction>[Persuade]</Start> Would 20 gold pieces refresh your memory?
